<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

<p>Participants must complete the following access and setup requirements before participating in the pilot.</p>

<h3>Required Access</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>GitHub Enterprise Access</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Request access through <strong>All Access</strong></li>
      <li>Complete the required GitHub security CBT</li>
      <li>Confirm access to the TGS Flow repository</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li><strong>GitHub Copilot</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Request a GitHub Copilot license through <strong>All Access</strong></li>
      <li>Complete the GitHub Copilot CBT</li>
      <li>Confirm Copilot is enabled in VS Code</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li><strong>Jira Access</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Request Jira access through <strong>All Access</strong></li>
      <li>Access to the required Jira project(s)</li>
      <li>Permission to create Epics and Stories</li>
      <li>Permission to assign issues</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li><strong>Confluence Access</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Request Confluence access through <strong>All Access</strong></li>
      <li>Access to the Confluence workspace containing pilot documentation</li>
      <li>Permission to view and comment on pilot documentation</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3>Local Development Requirements</h3>

<ul>
  <li>VS Code installed</li>
  <li>Git installed and configured</li>
  <li>Local Git repository available for testing</li>
  <li>GitHub token</li>
  <li>Jira token</li>
</ul>
